AMXD safety rule
- .amxd is not plain JSON.
- It is an ampf binary container; patcher JSON starts at byte offset 32.
- The ptch chunk length at byte offset 28 must be updated after length-changing edits.
- Never copy a .maxpat over an .amxd.
- Prefer the scripts in tools/ for AMXD edits.

Install / cleanup pipeline
- Reinstall the active Ableton preset and align the Max package with:
  powershell -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File tools\Install-CryptoSeqAbletonPreset.ps1 -ArchiveOtherCryptoSeqPresets
- This script backs up the current preset, archives other visible CryptoSeq*.amxd
  presets, copies the release AMXD, and updates package javascript/patchers/externals.

Persistence rules
- Live parameters need parameter_initial_enable = 1 for double-click reset.
- Defaults must live in parameter metadata, not hardcoded loadbang messages.
- Startup sync should send current control values to the engine after Live has
  restored saved device state.
- Use tools\Set-CryptoSeqParameterPersistence.ps1 after adding Live parameters.

Known UI/runtime decisions
- Hybrid mode uses pad count for Drum Rack pads; padcountindex fallback is needed
  so menu index 4 correctly maps to padcount 16 on startup.
- Morph is performance-critical and intentionally sends immediate setup for
  morphamount/morphscene/morphmode/morph to feel fluid.
- Other setup-heavy parameter changes should generally use debounce.
- Sequence and performance jsui panels coalesce redraws to reduce micro-lag.
- MIDI JS caches step duration and removes ratchet Tasks after they fire.
- Live Scale polling is intentionally slow (5000 ms) and should stay out of the
  MIDI-critical path.
- CRT Split is a core parameter exposed by Max message `crtsplit <symbol>`.
  Valid symbols are `off`, `p_pitch_q_rhythm`, `p_rhythm_q_pitch`, and
  `p_melody_q_drums`. It triggers immediate setup because it changes the
  musical identity of the generated pattern.

Architecture boundaries
- core/: deterministic generation.
- adapters/max/src + include/cryptoseq_max_model.*: Max-facing state/model
  without SDK dependency.
- adapters/max/src/cryptoseq_max_external.c: Max SDK bridge.
- adapters/max/javascript/: UI, routing, MIDI, Live API helpers.
- adapters/max/patchers/: Max patcher modules.
- release/: distributable Max package and AMXD copies.

Validation checklist after Max/M4L edits
- Inspect active/release AMXD with tools\Inspect-AmxdPatchcords.ps1.
- Dump parameter defaults with tools\Dump-CryptoSeqMaxParams.ps1 when changing UI controls.
- Confirm only one CryptoSeq*.amxd is visible in Ableton's Max MIDI Effect preset folder.
- Confirm active AMXD hash matches release AMXD when installing a release.
- Confirm package JS hashes match adapters/max/javascript sources after updates.
- In Ableton: load a fresh CryptoSeqALFA0.1-modular device, verify hybrid opens
  with pad count 16 actually sounding multiple pads, not only one.
- For CRT Split: in hybrid mode, compare `off`, `p_pitch_q_rhythm`, and
  `p_rhythm_q_pitch`; pad choices and active rhythm should change in different
  ways without changing the event output format.

Implemented feature: CRT Split
- Core enum: `cs_crt_split_t`.
- Core param: `cs_params_t.crt_split`, default `CS_CRT_SPLIT_OFF`.
- Model setter: `cs_max_model_set_crt_split`.
- External messages: `crtsplit`, `crtsplitmode`, and `crt`.
- Max UI parameter: `cs_crt_split_menu`, default `off`, in the performance panel.
- Tooling: `tools\Add-CryptoSeqCrtSplit.ps1` patches `.maxpat` and AMXD safely.
