Handoff: export button wiring repair
- 2026-07-01: export button was visible but did nothing. Root cause: the active
  AMXD had lost the patchcords from `obj-460` to the export chain.
- A first repair pass added bare line objects like
  `{"source":["obj-460",0],...}`. Max ignores those because valid patcher
  lines must be wrapped as `{"patchline":{...}}`.
- Fixed `tools\Add-CryptoSeqClipExport.ps1` so `Add-LineIfMissing` always
  appends wrapped `patchline` objects and preserves existing manual
  `presentation_rect` / `patching_rect` for `obj-460` and `obj-461`.
- Repaired active Ableton preset and release AMXDs. Current active/release
  hash:
  `A28E146F754AE77C97CBBD6594B822F055839AEC0D5F5D8F5C8CC7DCE6119324`.
- Active AMXD now has 134 boxes, 147 lines, and these export patchlines:
  `obj-460 -> obj-463 -> obj-219`, `obj-460 -> obj-464 -> obj-465 -> obj-462`,
  plus `obj-219`, `obj-2`, `obj-38`, and `obj-98` feeding `obj-462`.
- If testing in Ableton after this repair, remove/reinsert the device or
  restart Live so the patched AMXD is loaded.

