Handoff: empty exported clip fix
- 2026-07-01: user reported that export created an empty MIDI clip.
- Root cause addressed in `cryptoseq_clip_export.js`: note writing now tries
  the Live 11+ dictionary API first (`remove_notes_extended` +
  `add_new_notes`) and falls back to the legacy
  `replace_selected_notes` / `notes` / `note` / `done` path.
- The note dictionary is kept alive and reused instead of being freed right
  after `add_new_notes`, because Live API dict arguments are passed by name.
- Export status now reports `exporting <n>` before writing notes, so Ableton
  tests can distinguish "no events collected" from "write failed/empty clip".
- Live API clip ids are normalized from both `id 123` and `["id", 123]`
  forms before assigning `LiveAPI.id`.
- Export button dump delay was increased from 100 ms to 250 ms in
  `tools\Add-CryptoSeqClipExport.ps1` and all source/release/package patcher
  copies, giving the engine dump more time to populate the JS event cache.
- Installed the validated release into the active Ableton preset and Max
  package on 2026-07-01.
- Verification:
