Handoff: Sting 2 export comparison
- 2026-07-01: user reported exported MIDI clips still had no visible notes.
- Local reference checked:
  `C:\Users\asus\Documents\Ableton\User Library\Max4Live\Sting 2.amxd`.
- Sting 2 uses a Max patcher path with `dict` -> `prepend call add_new_notes`
  -> `live.object`. The important message shape is
  `call add_new_notes dictionary <dictname>`, not just
  `call add_new_notes <dictname>`.
- Fixed `cryptoseq_clip_export.js` to call:
  `clip.call("add_new_notes", "dictionary", dict.name)`.
- Also added the neutral Live note fields Sting includes:
  `probability: 1`, `velocity_deviation: 0`, `release_velocity: 64`.
  Do not add `note_id` for new notes.
- JS copies were synchronized across adapters, release folders, and installed
  Max package. Current `cryptoseq_clip_export.js` hash:
  `F54CC5E650E504C3367712A5C62AC092E9CB5B762944F02724E42D9238478820`.
